latestPosts.caption:
There’s something sacred about the way my mother cooks.

I’ve seen guests eat in silence, eyes wide, overwhelmed by a taste they’ve never known before. I can only hope to be half as good as her — in the kitchen, and in the way she makes people feel through her food.

If you’ve ever tasted my mom’s food — or hope to, one day — leave a comment below. I’ll read every word out to her. ❤️

Because here in Majuli, Assam — food is how we say, “Welcome home.”
